quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  86,1,"By the heaven, and At-Târiq (the night-comer, i.e. the bright star);"
  86,2,"And what will make you to know what At-Târiq (night-comer) is?"
  86,3,"(It is) the star of piercing brightness;"
  86,4,"There is no human being but has a protector over him (or her) (i.e. angels in charge of each human being guarding him, writing his good and bad deeds){1}",footnotes:1:1
  86,5,"So let man see from what he is created!"
  86,6,"He is created from a water gushing forth,"
  86,7,"Proceeding from between the backbone and the ribs."
  86,8,"Verily, (Allâh) is Able to bring him back (to life)!"
  86,9,"The Day when all the secrets (deeds, prayers, fasting, etc.) will be examined (as to their truth)."
  86,10,"Then he will have no power, nor any helper."
  87,1,"Glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most High,"
  87,2,"Who has created (everything), and then proportioned it."
  87,3,"And Who has measured (preordainments for everything even to be blessed or wretched); and then guided (i.e. showed mankind the right as well as the wrong paths, and guided the animals to pasture)."
  87,4,"And Who brings out the pasturage,"
  87,5,"And then makes it dark stubble."
  87,6,"We shall make you to recite (the Qur’ân), so you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) shall not forget (it),"
  87,7,"Except what Allâh may will. He knows what is apparent and what is hidden."
  87,8,"And We shall make easy for you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) the easy way (i.e. the doing of righteous deeds)."
  87,9,"Therefore remind (men) in case the reminder profits (them)."
  87,10,"The reminder will be received by him who fears (Allâh),"